## Tangle Process Implementation

### Setup Details
- Created Makefile with tangle/detangle targets
- Added :comments both to org-mode header-args for bidirectional sync
- Fixed .envrc to use direnv syntax instead of Python
- Mermaid diagrams tangle to .mmd files without comments (no comment syntax)

### Files Generated from PYTHON-GEMINI-REPL.org:
- Python source: src/gemini_repl/{__main__.py, core/, utils/, tools/}
- Configuration: .env.example, .envrc, requirements.txt
- Documentation: README.md, architecture.mmd, flow.mmd
- Infrastructure: Dockerfile, .github/workflows/ci.yml
- Scripts: setup.sh
- Tests: tests/test_repl.py

### Makefile Strategy
- Main Makefile handles tangle/detangle operations
- Tangled Makefile (Makefile.tangled) contains Python project targets
- Makefile.main preserves the tangle functionality across regenerations

### Known Issues
- Dockerfile and other non-standard languages lack comment syntax for org-babel
- Detangle requires manual Emacs interaction (C-c C-v C-d)
